Description: Sigmovir Biosystems Inc. is a Maryland-based biotechnology company.
Headquarters Regions: Washington DC Metro Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Sigmovir Biosystems, Inc. (SBI) is a Maryland-based biotechnology company specializing in the cotton rat model of human infectious diseases. Species of the cotton rat (genus Sigmodon) have been shown to be permissive for a wide array of human viral, bacterial, and parasitic pathogens. For the majority of these infectious agents, the cotton rat represents a more reliable model of human disease than the common murine strains and other small animal models. RSV, hPIV, Influenza, and HSV are among the best examples in this group. The validity of the model is best illustrated by the fact that prophylactic antibody treatment against severe RSV disease in infants advanced to clinical trials based on studies conducted in cotton rats alone, without the need for an additional testing in primates.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Accreditation is the independent evaluation of conformity assessment bodies against recognised standards to ensure their impartiality and competence. Through the application of national and international standards, government, procurers and consumers can have confidence in the calibration and test results, inspection reports and certifications provided. Accreditation bodies are established in many countries with the primary purpose of ensuring that conformity assessment bodies are subject to oversight by an authoritative body. Accreditation bodies, which have been evaluated by peers as competent, sign arrangements that enhance the acceptance of products and services across national borders, thereby creating a framework to support international trade through the removal of technical barriers. These arrangements are managed by the International Accreditation Forum (IAF), in the fields of management systems, products, services, personnel and other similar programmes of conformity assessment, and the International Laboratory Accreditation Cooperation (ILAC), in the field of laboratory and inspection accreditation.

Headquarters Regions: Greater San Diego Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Xcential is transforming the legislative and regulatory process, delivering cloud-enabled rulemaking software to the legislative branches and regulatory agencies of government. They transform the drafting, amending, publishing and codification of legislation and regulations from antiquated 19th and 20th century technology – pencils, paper, word processors and PDFs – into the machine-readable, cloud-ready and digitally efficient platform required by today’s citizens. They’re not system integrators or IT consultants: they’re a product company, focused on delivering solutions that transform the complicated tasks of drafting and codifying laws and regulations – increasing opportunities for greater efficiency, collaboration and transparency in the creation of content at the core of government. Delivered to our customers via “software as a service” (SaaS), our LegisPro product lines ease the transition to XML standards without the costly pain of years’-long IT overhaul projects and endless custom consulting contracts. Because we helped create the standards, our software works with the USLM and Akoma Ntoso/LegalDocML schemas. We’re specialists in content creation in structured data formats. That means our cloud-based software can be applied to the challenges of creating a range of government information required to be digital platform ready, from agency directives to policy statements, research reports and other legal material.

Full Description: Orchestra Medical Ventures (formerly Accelerated Technologies Partners) is an investment firm that employs a proprietary and innovative strategy to create, build and invest in medical technology companies intended to generate substantial clinical value and superior investor returns. Specifically, the Orchestra Strategy is based on coordinated collaboration with multi-disciplinary teams comprised of world-leading physicians and experienced technical and business experts. Working with these teams, Orchestra immerses itself into selected high-value, high-need clinical sectors in order to identify and analyze important unmet clinical needs that provide significant opportunities for technology innovations that can improve outcomes while reducing costs and complications. With these opportunities in mind, Orchestra and its sector-specific teams then work to conceive or source and then develop an optimal device solution to address such targeted unmet need. The Orchestra Strategy has been successfully pursued since 2000 through a predecessor medical device accelerator called Accelerated Technologies, Inc. Orchestra's distinctive aproach is designed to significantly improve the likelihood of success of investing in medical technology innovation by aligning the interests and harnessing the collective talent of physicians, management and investors from inception through value creation and realization.

Located in Olean, New York, the Olean Practical Nursing program gives students strong academics through classroom and lab training as well as clinical care experience in the field. Since Olean’s two-year Practical Nursing program is offered on a part-time basis, students may still work while going to school. An open-enrollment program, Olean’s Practical Nursing course admits anyone with a high school diploma or GED who is at least 16 years of age, and in certain circumstances will consider current high school students for admissions. Olean BOCES honors tuition assistance programs for veterans as well as the disabled, unemployed and underemployed. Additional financial aid resources are available to those who qualify through student loans, and may be discussed with an Olean BOCES financial aid representative.
